
[1]secretly

   SE'CRETLY, adv.

   1. Privately; privily; not openly; without the knowledge of others; as,
   to dispatch a messenger secretly.

   2. Inwardly; not apparently or visibly; latently.

   Now secretly with inward grief she pin'd. Addison.
